    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="359" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>According to the Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_464">p.
                        464</ref>, <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> called on
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> after <persName
                        corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName> had departed. No record has been found
                    of the remarks exchanged by <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> during this visit. That the
                    visit was short, and may have been limited to an exchange of courtesies, is
                    suggested by the fact that <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>’s
                    conversation with <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName>, which preceded
                    it, is stated in the <persName corresp="#p_BCE2">Bohlen</persName> minutes to
                    have ended at 4 o’clock, and the meeting which followed it is stated to have
                    begun at that same time. A brief reference to <persName corresp="#p_MVM1"
                        >Molotov</persName>’s call is in <persName corresp="#p_EW1">Elliott
                        Roosevelt</persName>, p. 176.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
